  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">West Japan Flooding Relief in Kurashiki, Okayama</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hundreds of thousands of families throughout West Japan have been affected by the heavy rains that have pummelled the area for over a week in early July. This has caused extensive flooding and landslides with over 200 deaths and many still missing. Operation Blessing Japan has started working in Mabi, Kurashiki in Okayama Prefecture, one of the hardest hit areas, and has launched a &quot;House Cleaning Team&quot;.</narrative>
  </description>
